723385f-a.text:
Spring Street, south side, from Renwick to Hudson Streets. Nos. 306-304, 302 Spring Street, at and adioining the Renwick Street corner, are frame houses with brick facing, and a brick wall on the Renwick Street side. No. 300, with the single dormer window, is solid brick; there were two more like it, one of frame, where the one-story store (after 1923) now stands.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 570.
